node.text: They say today is #NationalSmoresDay, but more importantly, it's wildfire season! Show me your creative side, how would you create delicious fireless s'mores at home? You can start with my delicious s'mores birthday cake recipe from my 75th birthday in 2019! Mmm.

node.text: I've been in so many videos about wildfire prevention over the lasty 74 years. Who remembers this cartoon from the1960s? #OnlyYou #SmokeyBear75

node.title: Smokey Bear and the Little Boy

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on August 27, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people standing, outdoors and text that says 'SMOKEY CA-CNF'.

node.text: This year's wildfire season has been intense, thank you to all of the wildland firefighters who have been working so hard to control the spread. (📷: @jordan.hante)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on August 25, 2021. May be an image of deer and text that says 'BEFORE YOU START ANY FIRE: FOLLOW LOCAL REGULATIONS .BE SURE FIRE CANT SPREAD DON'T BURN ON DRY, WINDY DAYS AND NEVER LEAVE FIRE UNATTENDED PLEASE! Only you can prevent forest fires'.

node.text: After a long year spent inside, we all want to get back outdoors. Remember - it's prime time for wildfires. Due to climate change, conditions are drier, temperatures are hotter, and the risk of sparking a wildfire is higher. Always check for burn bans and fire restrictions before you head out, and respect the instructions of local authorities.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on August 23, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'SMOKEY REMEMBER! only you can PREVENT WILD FIRES SMOKEY'.

node.text: Even @firstdoghenry knows that #OnlyYou can prevent wildfires.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on August 21, 2021.

node.text: Tiny Smokey on your keys is here to remind you not to park on dry grass. The heat from your exhaust could spark a fire. #OnlyYou can prevent wildfires. (📷: @metalandwood_co)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on August 18, 2021.

node.text: How many animal tracks can you spot in your home town? Our forests and wild lands are home to so many creatures, which is why we have to work together to prevent human-caused wildfires.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on August 16, 2021. May be an illustration.

node.text: When wildfires spread, we lose a lot more than just trees. Help prevent human-caused wildfires this year with helpful tips at SmokeyBear.com

node.text: They say today is #NationalSmoresDay, but more importantly, it's wildfire season! Show me your creative side, how would you create delicious fireless s'mores at home? You can start with my delicious s'mores birthday cake recipe from my 75th birthday in 2019! Mmm.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on August 09, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing and outdoors.

node.text: Today is my 77th birthday and I want to celebrate #OnlyYou! Thank you to all who share my wildfire prevention message for helping me to protect America's forests and wildlands. (📷: @mikerobinmcguire)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on August 07, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'Ta Smokey Says... DON'T KEEP IT LIT E XTINGUISH IT Ya'.

node.text: It's #NationalCampfireDay, do you remember how to extinguish a campfire? Say it with me: Drown, stir, down, feel! If the ashes are too hot to touch, it's too hot to leave.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on August 06, 2021. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text: Just 3 more days until my 77th birthday! The best gift you can give me is sharing my wildfire prevention tips with a friend. Visit SmokeyBear.com for helpful information to have in your back pocket when recreating outdoors this summer.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on August 02, 2021. May be a cartoon of standing and tree.

node.text: Did you know that you can design and download your own free Smokey Bear coloring book? Celebrate #NationalColoringBookDay by creating your own by visiting Smokey for Kids at SmokeyBear.com

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Smokey Bear on July 30, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing, tree and outdoors.

node.text: Anybody who helps prevent wildfires is a friend of mine. Happy #DayofFriendship, tag a friend who loves the environment as much as you do! (📷: @aubreyhays)
